Gareth Bale trained with a smile on his face as Chris Coleman’s Wales squad prepared for their crucial Euro 2016 clash in Israel.

The world’s most expensive player took part in light jogging exercises and skipped over mini hurdles amid the scenic surroundings of the Vale Resort in Cardiff.

The serene atmosphere was a world away from the heated scenes he left in Spain, where irate Real Madrid fans attacked his white Bentley in the early hours of Monday morning.

