Captain Ashley Williams said the players, including Bale, have fresh bills of health for the clash in Haifa.

‘Everyone is fit and ready,' said the Swansea defender. ‘The camp is buzzing. We had a good night on Monday seeing the guys we haven’t seen for a while.

‘We are looking to do some good work on the field this week and get the job done.’

Wales will fly to Tel Aviv on Thursday afternoon before travelling up to Haifa for the match at the Sammy Ofer Stadium between the top two teams in Group B.

